                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d354">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/985</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MRS1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-29T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 29, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Answering your January 22, 7 p.m., you may advise the Japanese Government: <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>That this Government has not been approached in regard to sending
                            Bolshevik envoys to replace Russian representatives now in this country
                            and will probably not be in a position to receive envoys <pb facs="0436"
                                n="362" xml:id="pg_362"/> from Russia until it establishes relations
                            with a government at Petrograd.</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>That the attitude of this Government and the people of the United
                            States towards Russia is expressed in the President’s address to
                            Congress and indicates a settled purpose to assist the Russian people
                            which is not contingent upon the acts of authorities in Russia not
                            recognized officially by the United States.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
